<br>
I finally picked up a manastone last week (paid 31k for it) and now I'm praying Verant doesn't nerf this.<br>
<br>
Manarobe plus epic is much rougher, about 260 mana every 60 seconds (vs 240 for just medding).  It's a touch faster, but very attention intensive.  If they changed the manarobe to a lich like effect kicking in once every 6 seconds (20 mana for 60 health) then you could use it while medding and it would really be nice.<br>
<br>
Note: all calculations ignore mana regained from innate regen, BoF, clarity, and/or flowing thought, and assume that triggering items and medding are mutually exclusive activities.  It also assumes that it takes 5 seconds to trigger manastone 13 times, and 45 seconds to do the same for manarobe (with 3.0 sec cast time). When you include innate regen and BoF effect, here are the mana regen rates without/with c2:<br>
<br>
Standing: 40/150 mana/min<br>
Meditate: 280/390 mana/min<br>
Manarobe: 300/410 mana/min<br>
Manastone: 820/930 mana/min<br>
Manarobe+: 400/510 mana/min  (liche like effect -- hypothetical item)<br>
<br>
- Armok Komra<br>
Sorcerer of Povar<br>
<br>
